<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870223-0155 </DOCNO><HL> McDonnell Unit GetsArmy Helicopter JobsTotaling $52.9 Million</HL><DD> 02/23/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MD TBO LK HPC GE GM GMHDEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   McDonnell Douglas Helicopter Co., a unit of McDonnell Douglas Corp., received Army contracts totaling $52.9 million for AH-64 helicopter logistics equipment and support.    Halter Marine Inc. received a $42.1 million Navy contract for three ocean-surveillance ships.    Tacoma Boatbuilding Co. received a $33.9 million Navy contract for an acoustic research ship.    American Development Corp. received a $20.5 million Army contract for bridge-erection boats.    Lockheed Corp. received an $18.8 million Air Force contract for C-130h aircraft equipment.    Hercules Inc. received a $16 million Army contract to operate a munitions plant at Radford, Va.    General Electric Co. received an $11.5 million Army contract for vehicle transmissions.    Hughes Aircraft Co., a unit of General Motors Corp., received a $10.7 million Army contract for TOW missile equipment for armored vehicles. </TEXT></DOC>